1
00:00:04,358 --> 00:00:10,873
A part of the Perfect
that appears to be imperfect.

2
00:00:10,873 --> 00:00:14,616
[Who are you? A Part of the Perfect]

3
00:00:15,168 --> 00:00:17,358
That’s all we are dealing with.

4
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:25,139
A part of the Perfect
appears to be imperfect.

5
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:29,100
That’s the material world 
in a nutshell.

6
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,940
And the material existence 
in a nutshell.

7
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:33,203
Just a part of the Perfect

8
00:00:33,939 --> 00:00:37,693
floating like an iceberg
in an ocean of consciousness.

9
00:00:38,061 --> 00:00:46,058
A part of the Perfect appears
to be imperfect from relative viewpoint—

10
00:00:46,526 --> 00:00:51,930
the false relative viewpoint
of acquired prejudice, acquired tendency,

11
00:00:51,930 --> 00:00:55,096
based upon exploiting tendencies.

12
00:00:56,498 --> 00:01:01,541
And so people of that ilk think 
they’re all about ‘self-expression’,

13
00:01:01,541 --> 00:01:05,773
and ‘I’ve just got to be me’.
[Laughing]

14
00:01:05,780 --> 00:01:10,918
Sure, you should be you,
but find out, who you are first.

15
00:01:10,918 --> 00:01:14,852
Don’t assume that
what you are at present,

16
00:01:14,852 --> 00:01:21,060
under layers of acquired prejudice,
acquired tendency and false ego,

17
00:01:22,768 --> 00:01:30,975
that false self, cocooning,
enveloping the actual self,

18
00:01:30,975 --> 00:01:37,093
is the self that’s worth
all of this self-expression.

